description.narrative: UNICEF Mozambique supported Government to implement the National Strategy for Basic Social Security 2016-2024 (ENSSB II), focusing on social protection programming through design, piloting and rigorous impact and process evaluation of child grant case management component, the design of child-sensitive social welfare services programs, social welfare workforce strengthening and the introduction of innovative case management models. The latter builds on an assessment that indicated the limited effectiveness of the community-based case management model. UNICEF Mozambique successfully enhanced government commitment to Alternative Care and increased number of children with disabilities benefitted emergency and recovery interventions after cyclone Idai and Kenneth. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
